value.0: A man's man. So beloved by the people of the city, and so renowned for his skill in architecture, it was little surprise that Thoven had been made a member of the Court despite his common upbringing.

Value.value: Yes, hello. Do you need something? We can arrange to speak with you later, if so.

value.0:
Once the chancellor of the Holy City and a former member of the Everguard, Gregory has since risen to leading the people of Fort Cystana. Unfortunately, upon the loss of the previous Justicar and dear friend Cystana, he keeps himself reserved and quiet. A chess piece dangles from his neck, showing proudly the faith he holds.

He was named King of Kohlingen, but his health forced him to abdicate.

This is a widget to add up to three permanent visuals to the PC upon use. It also has the functionality to up to three instant visuals on use.

Note: a basic understanding of the debug mode commands would be handy to set up this tool.

Apply instant visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx1 x and then target the widget, where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx2 and pc_vfx3 being the values for visuals two and three.

Apply permanent visuals by using the console command dm_setvarint pc_vfx_dur1 x and then target the widget , where x is the number of the visual. It goes up to 3, with pc_vfx_dur2 and pc_vfx_dur3 being the values for visuals two and three.
Fort Cystana's visionary mind. An aged yet strategic planner and adviser who serves as Council Chairman.

Value.value: *glances up* Ah, we are a bit busy, but if you wish to speak at a later time, I will gladly do so.

This noblewoman is in her mid-thirties, with lovely ash-blonde hair, and generally wears red and champagne gowns and cloaks of fine material. The Lady Johanna Evington is well-known as the Treasurer of the Court; she has a quick eye and a friendly demeanor.

She is renowned for her honesty, her intelligent grasp of the economy, and her swift and accurate collection of taxes. She seems very well-suited to her position and takes great pride in her work, as well as her knowledge.

Value.value: Greetings to you. I am bit occupied at the moment, but I will speak with you as soon as I possibly can. Take care.

value.0:
A distinguished gentleman stands before you, wearing a blue suit of luxurious materials and a fine brown cloak. Sir Winston is an older man, though not yet elderly, and still in fine shape. He sports a meticulous goatee and his black hair is peppered with grey.

He is renowned for his great political skill and gentility, particularly in  matters of public relations and foreign affairs, which has won him the admiration of the Court - this despite his well-known affairs with numerous mistresses, which are generally overlooked due to his considerable talents.

It is no secret that the passing of Lady Chimay has left Sir Winston depressed. Usually a jovial fellow, the loss has left his heart heavy and no amount of comforting seems able to break him out of it.

This silver-winged clerk works diligently to try to get things in order, moving back and forth between the counter and her work behind her.

Armor of this type began to appear in the lands adjacent to Thay in the Year of Smoldering Spells, 1020 DR. An irremovable coating of soot has blackened it, dulling noise of movement and making it ideal for stealthy endeavors. Close examination, however, reveals that the charring was not the result of externally applied heat, and suggests the original owner suffered some sort of Thayvian-induced combustion. This lends a very morbid feeling to the suit.

Caretaker of the Lady Anne Brionne and her baby brother Alexander, this nanny seems kindly, though she keeps a watchful eye on the children at all times. She is in her mid-sixties, with grey hair and green eyes, and generally wears robes of cream colors as befits her station and duties. She takes her responsibility seriously and does not hesitate to offer young lady Anne gentle lectures on acting as a young lady must.

This young lady, approximately 15 years of age, bears a striking resemblance to the Lady Marie Brionne. Indeed, this is her daughter, the Lady Anne, who, like her mother, has dark raven hair and stunning blue eyes and wears fine silks, usually in greenish hues. Most often seen with her caretaker when she is not studying with her private tutors, she normally spends her free time playing in the courtyard and watching speaks well and with confidence, is highly educated for her age, and is not in the least ashamed of making sure that everyone knows it.

Dressed in the garb of a court minstrel and often bearing an instrument, Philbert Mansen is well-known in Fort Cystana as the creator of many fine epic poems and songs. He has green eyes, is in his mid-thirties, and bears a well-kept goatee to complement his lush pomaded black hair and handsome features. He is well-mannered, treating those below him with civility and the nobility with appropriate deference, and so fast became a favorite to nearly the entire Court.  Reputed to have been a student at the Triumvir long ago, he came to the city in search of fame and glory - a quest at which he has clearly succeeded.

A young man around fifteen years old, Sir Cedric's squire is a loyal servant. He has warm brown eyes and brown hair pulled back into a neat ponytail. Since the passing of Sir Cedric, the young squire has been more withdrawn, but remains polite to those who approach him. He keeps near Sir Cuningham.

A veteran of various adventures across mainland Faerun, Lord Walter of House Mortimer stands as the last of his household. With nothing but a handfull of men to his name and his squire at his side, he returned home to Kohlingen to find it a burned ruin. Now, he holds the position of Lord Protector of the Kingdom of Kohlingen and seeks to right the wrongs inflicted upon his people.

This smooth, creamy  liquor is best served chilled. It comes in a  frothy pale fallow hue. It's rich flavor is heavily laden with gourmet chocolate and just a high light of hazelnut and hints of black cherry making this a truly decadent drink. It's sweet after taste leaves a warming sensation over the body making it a winter favorite.

This vivid, blood-red cocktail is made from bright-red sliced strawberries and raspberries. It come in a large , bowl-like glass. It is rich, with a sweet syrupy flavor of season's peak Strawberries and features highlights of Cherry, Raspberry and a smooth Orange cream. What really makes this drink interesting is the strange, small dark green glass bottle of champagne that it's served with. The small bottle is placed with in the large glass upside down and at a tilt upon the rim, as a decoration and bit of extra flair for those romantic evenings.

This smooth creamy drink comes in a large curved glass. The Drink itself has a lovely white and black motif that melts in to various shades of greys. Rich with authentic, Cormyrean Vanilla Ice cream this frosty drink  gives hints of white cake. The whole glass is topped with a lovely twirled dollop of sweet yet sharp chocolate flavored whipped cream and four vibrant, red Strawberries. This is a surprisingly strong drink for how innocent it tastes.

This colorful drink  holds dark amethyst, and deep, night-blue tones, that swirl and bleed together. The crushed ice of the drink creates the effect of stars in the night sky, only in your very own glass! The rim of this curvaceous glass is topped with vibrant, pink sugar, that tastes like cotton candy. This is a strong drink packed full of fruit flavors; Sweet Cherry, Blue Berry, and tart lemon all collide in to a wonderful melody for the tongue.

This 'jungle juice' is served not a glass but in a fresh, hallowed out pineapple. This fruity drink is strong with a mixture of rums known best from the region of Chult. Pineapple, Peach, and Orange are the  primary flavors of this fantastically fruity cocktail with just a splash of cherry, grapefruit, and lime. It is topped with a disk of an orange slice, followed by a lime slice with a cherry on top and a small paper umbrella for decoration. Don't be fooled by the colorful appearance this is a very potent drink.

This neon green drink comes in a shapely glass with a high stem. The rim of the glass is served with  acid green sugar which tastes like tart, sour-apple. The glass is decorated with slices of Kiwi around the sides and offers a sweet yet empowered flavor of Karaturan melon liquor, mixed with hints of Strawberries, Kiwis and just a touch of Green Tea for highlight. A slice of kiwi decorated the edge of the glass. The drink is thick and smooth made from a blended slush. The very top of the drink is highlighted with a touch of vivid blue Liquor that offers a sweet blue berry flavor.
